body:
Something else to keep in mind - there are GPU implementations for SVD, QR, Solve, etc available through cuSolver. These will be more efficient if svd were a buitkin function rather than a DML bodied function.  

@j143 - you can take a look at PR #273 also, it has an earlier attempt at this. 

Having a "local" svd is good. The distributed version can be built as a Builtin function or as a DML bodies function. The advantage of the DML bodied distributed version is that it can use the GPU implementation as it's building blocks.

@j143 - are you planning on following up on the implementation of `svd()` in a new PR?


As per your request on PR #273, I've rebased my svd branch against master - https://github.com/nakul02/systemml/tree/svd


Please note that as more commits are added to master, it may soon become stale. If you plan to use this to continue working on `svd()`, please clone my svd branch to your fork/clone of the systemml repo and rebase that.
